    "name": "Mesh independence study for VAD centrifugal pump CFD model",
    "description": "Systematic mesh refinement study conducted across four mesh densities (0.8M, 2.1M, 5.4M, and 12.7M cells) to establish discretization-independent hemolysis index predictions. Richardson extrapolation applied to quantify grid convergence index (GCI) for the primary QoI. Study performed at the nominal operating point (5 L/min, 3600 RPM) and two off-design conditions. Convergence criterion: GCI < 2% on normalized hemolysis index.",
    "activityType": "MeshRefinementStudy",
